Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Place a few @Salad Potatoes{350%g} at a time in between two #wooden spoon{} handles on a #board{}. Make slices widthways at 3mm intervals, making sure not to cut the whole way through. Repeat with the remaining potatoes.

Put the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Lemon{1/2}. Finely chop the @Dill{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all).

Pop the dill and @Capers{15} into a #small bowl{} and add the @Olive Oil{2}(for the salsa). Squeeze in some lemon juice, then season with @salt and @ground black pepper.

Taste and add more salt, pepper or lemon juice if needed. Set your salsa aside for now.

Pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} and @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%g} onto another baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and set aside.

About 15 mins before the potatoes are ready, remove the #potato tray{} from the oven and move the potatoes to one side.

Lay the @Salmon Fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto the other side of the #baking tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Roast for the remaining time until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

At the same time, roast the veg on the middle shelf of your oven until the broccoli is tender and the tomatoes are soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When everything's ready, plate up your salmon with the hasselbacks and roasted veg alongside.

Spoon the salsa over the salmon to finish. Enjoy!